result.execSummary:
The defendant Randall A. Hastings was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Escape-Criminal Arrest, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.42(3)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Randall A. Hastings in court.  Attorney Mark Walter Frank in court for Randall A. Hastings.  Attorney Anthony Joseph Pozorski Sr. in court for State of Wisconsin. Per agreement, defendant to plead to all counts. As to Count 3, six months jail. Remaining counts two years probation, costs, counseling, DNA, no contact with TB without permission of agent. Court reviews plea questionnaire and finds defendant freely and knowingly waives his rights. Defendant pleads no contest. Court reviews felony loss of rights. Court accepts pleas and finds defendant guilty of all counts. State heard. Attorney Frank heard. Defendant heard. Court orders 6 months jail with huber on Count 3, imposed and stayed, with two years probation. All other counts, two years probation with conditions: One set court costs, DNA, counseling, agent to determine contact with TB. If revoked, 11 days credit.
